sql:
SELECT products.product_name, product_types.product_type_name
FROM products
JOIN product_types ON products.product_type_id = product_types.product_type_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Captain of their own financial voyage' is a metaphorical way to refer to a customer in control of their spending behavior;
- 'Treasure chests' is a metaphor for 'orders', symbolizing the accumulation of items purchased;
- 'Golden doubloons' is a metaphor for 'total spent' money, symbolizing the value accumulated from all purchases;
- 'Plundered' is a metaphor for 'placed orders' or 'made purchases', suggesting an adventurous and active role in the act of buying.

sql:
SELECT product_name, description
FROM products
WHERE product_id = (SELECT MAX(product_id) FROM products);

external_knowledge:
- "burst forth from the seedbed of abundance" refers to products with a volume over 10 ounces;
- "customer raindrops who have watered the garden of commerce" metaphorically refers to customers who have made significant purchases;
- "since the dawn of the new lunar year" alludes to orders placed after January 1, 2023;
- "seeds have been sown" means the order status is 'shipped'.
